  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Gelatin tannate possesses astringent, antibacterial, and anti-inflammatory properties. It is
      increasingly being marketed as an antidiarrheal drug. A randomized, double blind,
      placebo-control trial was performed to assess the effectiveness of GT in management of
      children with acute gastroenteritis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
